textBeforeTable: Download portaudio19-dev Portable audio I/O - shared library libportaudio2 (= 19+svn20071022-3.2) dep: libjack-dev, libjack-jackd2-dev virtual package provided by libjack0.100.0-dev [i386, powerpc] dep: liboss-salsa-dev also a virtual package provided by shared library for ALSA applications -- development files libasound2-dev [not kfreebsd-amd64, kfreebsd-i386] dep: enhances suggests recommends depends Other Packages Related to portaudio19-dev Tags: Software Development: Libraries, Role: Development Library This package contains the development files. PortAudio is a portable audio I/O library designed for cross-platform support of audio. It uses a callback mechanism to request audio processing. Audio can be generated in various formats, including 32 bit floating point, and will be converted to the native format internally.
